{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_4","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' .claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-14-cross-path-task1-review.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Evolution Note — Cross-Path Task 1 Review\n\n## Plan\n\n- path: `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md`\n- milestone: `Milestone 3 — Insight and Guidance Layer (complete)`\n- bounded target: review whether path-origin visibility is now sufficient to move from path labeling into cross-path filtering\n\n## Completed\n\n- Reviewed the current Task 1 path-identity work on the cross-path unified management track\n- Confirmed thread rows and spotlight now both expose a compact root identity while still preserving access to the full path text\n- Closed the current Task 1 visibility concern and re-anchored the track to a Task 2 filtering audit instead of continuing to add path labels to more surfaces\n\n## Failed or Deferred\n\n- No code changes were made in this review slice\n- No packaging run was needed because extension behavior did not change\n- Deferred any third-surface path-label parity because Task 1 visibility is sufficiently advanced for now\n\n## Decisions\n\n- Treat Task 1 as sufficiently advanced once the main scan surface and main inspection surface both expose compact root identity\n- Move next to cross-path filtering, which is the next least-implemented task in the published task-plan\n\n## Next Handoff\n\n```text\nContinue the codex-loop from `.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md` using `ROADMAP.md` as the anchor. Stay on the cross-path unified management track and do one Task 2 audit focused on the first smallest cross-path filtering gap, then update the active plan, append a new evolution note, and sync to `/home/clashuser/hzh/work_bo/codex_manager/vscode-extension`.\n```\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
